Package InfrastructureManager.Modules.AdvantEDGE.Output.NetworkCharacteristic

Class NetworkParameters

java.lang.Object
InfrastructureManager.Modules.AdvantEDGE.Output.NetworkCharacteristic.NetworkParameters
public class NetworkParameters
extends java.lang.Object
Class to model the different network characteristics that can be applied in AdvantEdge to Scenarios, Domains, Zones, among other elements.

These effectively allow to simulate changes in the network in an edge deployment.

The class wraps all possible network characteristics and provides setters and getters for each of them.

  • Constructor Details

    • NetworkParameters

      public NetworkParameters​(int throughputDl, int throughputUl, int latency, int latencyVariation, int packetLoss)
      Creates a new NetworkParameters object based on the different network characteristics
      Parameters:
      throughputDl - Maximum amount of data moved between two points in the network (DownLink direction) (Mbps)
      throughputUl - Maximum amount of data moved between two points in the network (UpLink direction) (Mbps)
      latency - Amount of time that a packet takes to traverse a network to its final destination (ms)
      latencyVariation - Variation of the latency parameter (ms)
      packetLoss - Packet loss occurs when data packets travelling across the network fail to reach their destination (%)
